This is a simple Python project to manage patient health records using a command-line interface.
It helps users add patients, store health records, manage medicines, and generate health reports easily.
All data is saved in a SQLite database, so information is not lost after closing the program.

Features

Add new patients with name, age, and gender
View all registered patients
Add health records (BP, Sugar, Weight, Date)
View patient health history
Add medicine schedule
View medicines for each patient
Generate health summary report
Delete patient records

Technologies Used:

Python
SQLite Database
SQL Queries
File Handling
Command Line Interface (CLI)

How This Project Works
The program connects to the caretrack.db database file.
Required tables are created automatically if they do not exist.
A menu is shown to the user.

User selects an option:
Add Patient
View Patients
Add Health Record
View Health Records
Add Medicine
View Medicines
Health Report
Delete Patient
Exit

Based on the choice, the program performs the action.
All data is saved automatically in the database.
Database File Used
caretrack.db
This file stores all patient, record, and medicine data in SQLite format.
